## ğŸ“˜ FIPS 199 â€“ Security Impact Categories

| Impact Level | Description                                                                 |
|--------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| **Low**      | Limited adverse effect (minor inconvenience or operational disruption)     |
| **Moderate** | Serious adverse effect (harm to operations, finances, or privacy)           |
| **High**     | Severe or catastrophic impact (loss of life, critical missions, legal harm) |

### ğŸ¥ Case Study: OpenMRS (Electronic Medical Records System)

Hereâ€™s how I evaluated the impact levels for OpenMRS in a clinical environment:

| Security Objective | Impact Level | Justification                                                                                 |
|--------------------|--------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| **Confidentiality**| High         | Exposure of PHI (e.g. HIV status, mental health data) could cause **serious harm** and violate HIPAA |
| **Integrity**      | High         | Tampering with records could lead to **incorrect treatments or diagnoses**                     |
| **Availability**   | Moderateâ€“High| Downtime could **delay care**, especially in under-resourced clinics without paper backups     |

> âœ… As a GRC leader, I categorize OpenMRS as a **High-Impact System**, demanding **rigorous security controls, increased oversight, and continuous monitoring**.

